body_html: @Ecolow : Unfortunately, the syntaxnet model that you're using is currently pinned to a specific snapshot of the TensorFlow repository and it does not update with changes to the TensorFlow repository. So, the workaround for now would be to remove testonly=1 from the snapshot of the TensorFlow repository it uses - (inside tensorflow/models/syntaxnet/tensorflow/tensorflow/python/BUILD)

body: @Ecolow : Unfortunately, the syntaxnet model that you're using is currently pinned to a specific snapshot of the TensorFlow repository and it does not update with changes to the TensorFlow repository. So, the workaround for now would be to remove `testonly=1` from the snapshot of the TensorFlow repository it uses - (inside `tensorflow/models/syntaxnet/tensorflow/tensorflow/python/BUILD`)
